Syllabus_Link:
At the conclusion of this course and with sufficient study and regular attendance, students are expected to develop the following skills and knowledge base of:
•  The criminal investigation elements and process
•  The types of criminal investigations and the resources needed to conduct them
•  The importance of evidence and crime scene management
•  Proper interviewing of suspects, victims, and witnesses
•  Writing a criminal investigations report
•  The construction, application, and service of search and arrest warrants
•  How multi-jurisdictional task forces operate & describe the benefits of utilizing resources from various agencies
